and we'll call you back.

31:02.260 --> 31:04.730
Have a great day.
[answering machine beeps]

31:04.763 --> 31:07.265
‐ Ryan, Anthony.

31:08.433 --> 31:10.202
I'm just gonna call back
and call back

31:10.235 --> 31:12.270
until someone turns
the ringer on.

31:12.304 --> 31:13.572
[line clicks]

31:13.605 --> 31:16.742
‐ Don't you even care
about your family?

31:16.775 --> 31:18.910
Besides the stupid money?

31:19.845 --> 31:21.780
‐ I care perfectly
about my family.

31:21.813 --> 31:23.148
‐ Then how come you don't
shut your mouth

31:23.181 --> 31:24.683
so we can come over there?

31:24.716 --> 31:26.585
[faint beeping]

31:26.618 --> 31:27.886
‐ Who's on this phone?

31:27.919 --> 31:30.088
‐ Me.
‐ No, I just heard something.

31:30.122 --> 31:31.823
‐ Nobody's on the phone.

31:31.857 --> 31:33.792
‐ What is that noise?

31:33.825 --> 31:35.327
‐ What noise?

31:35.360 --> 31:37.229
‐ People walking around.

31:37.262 --> 31:39.598
‐ Like, Anthony and Dad
and stuff.

31:39.631 --> 31:40.699
‐ Stuff?
You mean the whore's there?

31:40.732 --> 31:41.700
‐ No!

31:41.733 --> 31:43.602
Why can't you just mind
your own business

31:43.635 --> 31:45.771
and not care who he's seeing?

31:45.804 --> 31:47.506
He could be seeing
a totally different girl

31:47.539 --> 31:49.341
and it wouldn't matter.
‐ Congratulations.

31:49.374 --> 31:50.942
You've been living with him
too long.

31:50.976 --> 31:52.144
You don't have any values.

31:52.177 --> 31:53.845
Right, wrong,
truth, lie.

31:53.879 --> 31:55.347
You stay there,

31:55.380 --> 31:57.282
your whole head's
gonna go to scrambled eggs.

31:57.315 --> 31:58.283
[scoffs]

31:58.316 --> 32:00.652
Two years, I put up with
this shit in my face.

32:00.685 --> 32:02.988
‐ Look, it's not
only Linda's fault.

32:03.021 --> 32:05.157
It's Dad's fault, too,
and it's your fault.

32:05.190 --> 32:07.526
‐ Listen, when he took
you guys from me‐‐

32:07.559 --> 32:10.095
‐ He didn't take us away.
You gave us to him.

32:10.128 --> 32:11.830
‐ And you've been having a
great time ever since, right?

32:11.863 --> 32:13.532
‐ No, we haven't!

32:13.565 --> 32:15.000
We've been having
a horrible time!

32:15.033 --> 32:15.967
‐ Why don't you
just stay there?

32:16.001 --> 32:17.969
‐ You don't want us to,
though, Mom.

32:18.003 --> 32:19.504
‐ [scoffs]
‐ And we wanna be with you.

32:19.538 --> 32:21.840
If you just stop saying
bad words,

32:21.873 --> 32:23.975
then everyone would be happier.

32:24.009 --> 32:26.545
I know I will
and Anthony will.

32:26.578 --> 32:28.713
‐ Meanwhile the whore's
allowed to be around you.

32:28.747 --> 32:30.916
‐ You guys are divorced!

32:30.949 --> 32:33.251
Dad can be with anyone
he wants to!

32:33.285 --> 32:35.987
‐ Daddy's divorced.
I'm still married.

32:36.021 --> 32:37.923
‐ Well, he likes
somebody else now.

32:37.956 --> 32:39.991
‐ You're just gonna get
madder and madder

32:40.025 --> 32:41.593
and you're the only one
who can fix it.

32:41.626 --> 32:44.062
‐ [laughs] If Dan Broderick
wants to settle,

32:44.095 --> 32:45.864
he can do it in an hour.
‐ How?

32:45.897 --> 32:47.899
You want all the kids
and all the money

32:47.933 --> 32:49.167
and Linda to go away,

32:49.201 --> 32:50.802
and that leaves Dad
with nothing.

32:50.836 --> 32:53.205
‐ Excuse me?
He walked away!

32:53.238 --> 32:55.073
What do I care
if he ends up with nothing?

32:55.106 --> 32:57.275
‐ Oh, okay.
What does he care if you do?

32:57.309 --> 32:59.845
All I care about is
I wanna come live there

32:59.878 --> 33:01.913
and Anthony wants to, too.

33:01.947 --> 33:02.848
[faint clicking]

33:02.881 --> 33:04.916
‐ Somebody's on this phone.
‐ No!

33:04.950 --> 33:07.519
‐ Ryan, you don't
understand things.

33:07.552 --> 33:08.854
‐ You don't either, Mom!

33:08.887 --> 33:12.958
Why can't you just grow up
and start acting like a woman?

33:12.991 --> 33:14.693
You want everything your way.

33:14.726 --> 33:16.695
‐ I haven't had
anything my way.

33:16.728 --> 33:19.164
Daddy robbed me of everything
I had on Earth.

33:19.197 --> 33:21.867
He ‐‐‐‐‐‐ your whole life
and my whole life.

33:21.900 --> 33:24.469
‐ You're doing
the same thing, Mom!

33:24.503 --> 33:25.804
You've been mad long enough!

33:25.837 --> 33:27.939
‐ Oh, no, I haven't.

33:27.973 --> 33:31.877
[dramatic music]

33:31.910 --> 33:39.050
♪ ♪

33:39.451 --> 33:41.620
‐ [sighs]

33:41.653 --> 33:48.226
♪ ♪

33:49.261 --> 33:51.129
‐ Wanna go watch some TV?

33:51.162 --> 33:52.998
‐ Yeah.
‐ Yeah?

33:53.031 --> 33:55.000
You tell Tracy
I said it's okay.

33:55.033 --> 34:02.207
♪ ♪

34:09.614 --> 34:12.584
[exhales sharply]

34:12.617 --> 34:19.591
♪ ♪

34:44.716 --> 34:45.216
‐ [laughing]
‐ Okay, okay.

34:46.251 --> 34:47.085
You can have that day off
but you have to be ready

34:47.118 --> 34:49.454
to go out by seven.
‐ Ready for what?

34:49.487 --> 34:50.822
Where are we going?
‐ Out.

34:50.855 --> 34:52.657
‐ Out? Where?
Just tell me.

34:52.691 --> 34:54.292
‐ How is it a surprise
if I tell you?

34:54.326 --> 34:55.627
But you're gonna like it.

34:55.660 --> 34:57.896
‐ [laughs]
‐ Hey.

34:57.929 --> 34:59.464
It's a long one,
so take your time.

34:59.497 --> 35:01.933
It's important.

35:01.967 --> 35:03.301
‐ And then on top
of the clothes

35:03.335 --> 35:05.870
and the nails and the colds
and the lice,

35:05.904 --> 35:09.808
his ears were just filled
with wax.

35:09.841 --> 35:11.142
The Count Du Money
is so perfect

35:11.176 --> 35:13.211
about his own appearance
but he doesn't care

35:13.244 --> 35:15.747
if his own kids walk around
filthy and sick

35:15.780 --> 35:17.849
probably because he thinks
if anyone sees them that way,

35:17.882 --> 35:19.818
they'll blame me.
‐ Okay.

35:24.189 --> 35:26.157
‐ You said you only
see a parent once,

35:26.191 --> 35:28.093
yet here I am again.

35:28.126 --> 35:31.429
‐ I did feel that we should
have another session.

35:31.463 --> 35:34.265
One that was
a little more structured,

35:34.299 --> 35:37.969
and our previous meeting became
a chance for you to vent.

35:38.003 --> 35:40.872
‐ I have a lot to vent.
‐ Which I appreciate.

35:40.905 --> 35:44.075
But I also have certain things
that I am supposed

35:44.109 --> 35:46.578
to accomplish in here.
‐ Like what?

35:46.611 --> 35:49.848
‐ Like if you were
to get the children back.

35:49.881 --> 35:53.251
I mean, if that could be worked
out for that to happen,

35:53.284 --> 35:57.122
what kind of visitation would
you want Mr. Broderick to have?

35:57.155 --> 35:59.591
‐ No visitation.

35:59.624 --> 36:02.060
And no notes.

36:02.093 --> 36:03.194
‐ Okay.

36:05.163 --> 36:08.133
[tense music]

36:08.166 --> 36:10.335
♪ ♪

36:10.368 --> 36:13.405
‐ I was a good mother always.

36:13.438 --> 36:14.773
I was always there.

36:14.806 --> 36:17.108
I did everything
I was supposed to do.

36:17.142 --> 36:19.210
♪ ♪

36:19.244 --> 36:21.579
For years,
my parenting abilities

36:21.613 --> 36:23.581
were fine by Dan Broderick.

36:23.615 --> 36:25.483
Now we're in litigation,
suddenly, they're not.

36:25.517 --> 36:26.451
‐ That's why we're here.

36:26.484 --> 36:29.754
‐ He didn't care
if they were eaten by rats.

36:29.788 --> 36:32.791
He didn't care
if they saw his whore

36:32.824 --> 36:34.592
with her legs spread
in the hallway...

36:34.626 --> 36:36.327
‐ We‐‐
‐ Or how many times‐‐

36:36.361 --> 36:37.862
‐ What's her name?

36:37.896 --> 36:39.564
‐ Wait, what?
Who?

36:39.597 --> 36:41.633
♪ ♪

36:41.666 --> 36:43.601
I don't care.
I don't care.

36:43.635 --> 36:46.004
I mean, does she care about me?
Does she care about my kids?

36:46.037 --> 36:48.540
‐ Did you discuss
any of this with her?

36:48.573 --> 36:51.409
I mean,
try telling her anything?

36:51.443 --> 36:54.779
Even‐‐even in anger.
‐ Oh, that's on me to do too?

36:54.813 --> 36:58.116
♪ ♪

36:58.149 --> 36:59.884
[scoffs]

37:04.656 --> 37:06.024
Linda.

37:06.057 --> 37:07.792
‐ Ah.

37:09.294 --> 37:10.795
‐ Linda.

37:10.829 --> 37:17.702
♪ ♪

37:17.736 --> 37:19.337
All right?
‐ Mm‐hmm.

37:23.007 --> 37:25.210
‐ [stammers]
Are you all right?

37:25.243 --> 37:26.978
‐ I'm done.

37:27.011 --> 37:29.314
I'm not coming back here again.
You're too good at this.

37:29.347 --> 37:31.282
You're too good at what you do.
You're too good of a therapist.

37:31.316 --> 37:33.218
I don't want those kids
by myself.

37:33.251 --> 37:34.853
I won't let you
talk me into it.

37:34.886 --> 37:36.721
You make me forget that
I'm angry at the asshole

37:36.755 --> 37:38.690
and his whore,
and if I'm not angry,

37:38.723 --> 37:40.358
I'm not gonna make it.

37:45.363 --> 37:47.031
[door slams]

37:47.065 --> 37:50.235
‐ The hearing's tomorrow
and I need background, Betty,

37:50.268 --> 37:52.670
on all these contempt motions
they sent over.

37:52.704 --> 37:54.072
I thought you told me

37:54.105 --> 37:55.306
you wouldn't call Dan
or harass him anymore.

37:55.340 --> 37:58.143
‐ Yeah, right, I'm the only one
expected to keep my promises.

37:58.176 --> 37:59.210
I forgot.

37:59.244 --> 38:02.046
‐ All right, well,
speaking of that,

38:02.080 --> 38:05.550
I've been trying not
to bring this up,

38:05.583 --> 38:08.153
but I still haven't been paid.

38:08.186 --> 38:10.388
So I have a proposition
for you.

38:10.421 --> 38:13.992
I found out that Dan's selling
one of the Colorado properties.

38:14.025 --> 38:16.327
‐ What?
‐ And long story short,

38:16.361 --> 38:19.697
Dan's agreed to send me a check
for the full amount of sale.

38:19.731 --> 38:21.499
Let me act as broker,

38:21.533 --> 38:24.002
divide the proceeds
between the two of you,

38:24.035 --> 38:27.105
and take my fee from your half.

38:27.138 --> 38:29.240
What do you think?
‐ Dan has agreed?

38:30.608 --> 38:32.877
What does that mean?

38:32.911 --> 38:34.212
Did you talk to Dan?

38:34.245 --> 38:35.380
‐ I called him first
to ask him‐‐

38:35.413 --> 38:38.183
‐ Why is my lawyer

38:38.216 --> 38:40.685
talking to Dan Broderick
without even telling me?

38:40.718 --> 38:42.954
‐ I did try to explain this
to you‐‐

38:42.987 --> 38:45.423
‐ Oh, God, you're just like
all the others, I guess‐‐

38:45.456 --> 38:47.792
wanna get in good with him
at my expense!

38:47.826 --> 38:49.694
‐ You don't have
to listen to me, Betty.

38:49.727 --> 38:51.196
That's your right,

38:51.229 --> 38:53.798
but I am not going
to work for free.

38:53.832 --> 38:56.668
So you tell me, then.
What do we do?

38:56.701 --> 38:59.304
♪ ♪

38:59.337 --> 39:01.739
‐ I understand you will
no longer be serving

39:01.773 --> 39:03.541
as council for Mrs. Broderick,
Ms. Clark.

39:03.575 --> 39:06.044
‐ That's correct, Your Honor,
at Mrs. Broderick's request.

39:06.077 --> 39:07.912
‐ The court is grateful
for your appearance today.

39:07.946 --> 39:10.181
‐ Sir, if I could
go on the record,

39:10.215 --> 39:12.984
these contempt filings
and postponements

39:13.017 --> 39:15.220
by Mr. Mills and Mr. Broderick

39:15.253 --> 39:18.489
serve to deliberately delay
trial proceedings,

39:18.523 --> 39:20.491
which will of course dilute
Mrs. Broderick's share

39:20.525 --> 39:24.596
of community property either
by accruing undue debts

39:24.629 --> 39:26.130
or even hiding assets.

39:26.164 --> 39:28.633
‐ Excuse me.
‐ Which I find surprising,

39:28.666 --> 39:30.568
after Mr. Mills
and Mr. Broderick

39:30.602 --> 39:32.770
have assured me countless times

39:32.804 --> 39:35.173
that Mr. Broderick wishes only

39:35.206 --> 39:37.942
to equally divide the property
and get on with his life.

39:37.976 --> 39:40.645
‐ These are unfounded
accusations, Your Honor.

39:40.678 --> 39:43.681
‐ I want to talk about how,

39:43.715 --> 39:45.416
after I made myself
very clear,

39:45.450 --> 39:50.121
I somehow again have a calendar
of backed up contempt motions

39:50.154 --> 39:51.256
against your client, Ms. Clark.

39:51.289 --> 39:54.259
Nine different new ones
in the system.

39:54.292 --> 39:55.860
Five that Mrs. Broderick
needs to answer

39:55.894 --> 39:57.629
in this hearing today,

39:57.662 --> 40:01.399
and that's on top of 24 days
worth of suspended sentences

40:01.432 --> 40:03.167
from previous contempt
convictions.

40:03.201 --> 40:06.137
‐ I would argue
it is blatantly inflammatory

40:06.170 --> 40:08.840
for Miss Kolkena to record
the outgoing message

40:08.873 --> 40:09.941
for the Broderick household,

40:09.974 --> 40:14.012
that it causes Mrs. Broderick
to become emotional

40:14.045 --> 40:16.047
and express herself badly.
‐ Oh, stop.

40:16.080 --> 40:18.549
Stop.
I am done with this.

40:18.583 --> 40:19.584
[pages turning]

40:19.617 --> 40:22.453
Get the girlfriend
off the machine.

40:22.487 --> 40:24.555
Now,

40:24.589 --> 40:26.090
moving on to the children.

40:26.124 --> 40:28.259
Having reviewed and considered

40:28.293 --> 40:30.295
the detailed
therapeutic assessment

40:30.328 --> 40:31.930
of Mrs. Broderick's
mental health,

40:31.963 --> 40:33.965
I am officially
sanctioning matters

40:33.998 --> 40:36.668
to remain as they are.
‐ [exhales]

40:36.701 --> 40:39.637
‐ Mr. Broderick shall retain
sole custody

40:39.671 --> 40:42.573
with visitation to Mrs.
Broderick at his discretion.

40:42.607 --> 40:44.309
And Mrs. Broderick?

40:44.342 --> 40:46.511
I'm imposing
a 25‐day jail sentence.

40:46.544 --> 40:49.347
‐ Your Honor, I understand
your frustration and‐‐

40:49.380 --> 40:51.716
and desire to hold
Mrs. Broderick accountable.

40:51.749 --> 40:52.951
I do.

40:52.984 --> 40:56.688
But a sentence of such length
will not be rehabilitative.

40:56.721 --> 40:59.524
If‐‐if Mrs. Broderick‐‐if‐‐

40:59.557 --> 41:02.393
if she perhaps apologized
to the court...

41:02.427 --> 41:05.396
[tense music]

41:05.430 --> 41:12.136
♪ ♪

41:16.174 --> 41:19.877
‐ Judge Russell,
I promise to change my ways.

41:19.911 --> 41:21.946
I do know what
you don't want me to do.

41:21.980 --> 41:26.918
♪ ♪

41:26.951 --> 41:30.254
I've just been trying
to escape this madness.

41:30.288 --> 41:33.291
‐ 19 days suspended.
Six days in jail.

41:33.324 --> 41:35.693
‐ Your Honor,
I respectfully request a stay

41:35.727 --> 41:38.429
for Mrs. Broderick to go home
and get her affairs in order.

41:38.463 --> 41:40.965
‐ Denied.

41:40.999 --> 41:48.172
♪ ♪

41:59.117 --> 42:00.718
‐ [exhales]

42:00.752 --> 42:03.221
Hey, bud.

42:03.254 --> 42:05.390
Jen told me I should come
talk to you.

42:05.423 --> 42:07.658
Said you were crying earlier.

42:07.692 --> 42:09.794
Wouldn't tell anybody why.

42:09.827 --> 42:12.663
‐ Mom.

42:12.697 --> 42:15.433
I mean, if we're never gonna
get to be with her,

42:15.466 --> 42:16.968
live with her...

42:17.001 --> 42:18.603
‐ Ryan‐‐
‐ We need her.

42:18.636 --> 42:20.104
And she needs us.

42:20.138 --> 42:23.007
‐ I know.
I know it's hard.

42:23.041 --> 42:27.678
♪ ♪

42:27.712 --> 42:30.181
You're a kid,

42:30.214 --> 42:32.483
and your mom
is like a kid, too.

42:32.517 --> 42:34.318
♪ ♪

42:34.352 --> 42:36.120
She doesn't get her way,

42:36.154 --> 42:38.956
she kicks and screams,
breaks things.

42:38.990 --> 42:41.292
Okay, okay.
Just a little more.

42:41.325 --> 42:43.027
A little‐‐little further.
Little further.

42:43.061 --> 42:44.295
Don't move.

42:44.328 --> 42:46.564
Stay right there.
‐ [giggles]

42:46.597 --> 42:48.466
[both chuckling]

42:50.101 --> 42:52.336
‐ Okay, take the blindfold off.

42:52.370 --> 42:56.107
♪ ♪

42:56.140 --> 42:59.243
Will you marry me?

42:59.277 --> 43:01.846
‐ [softly]
Yes.

43:01.879 --> 43:03.047
‐ She said yes!

43:03.081 --> 43:06.050
[cheers and applause]

43:06.084 --> 43:12.890
♪ ♪

43:12.924 --> 43:15.993
She just can't control herself.

43:16.027 --> 43:19.497
She's never been able to.
She's always been this way.

43:19.530 --> 43:21.065
[sighs]

43:21.099 --> 43:22.633
She just can't stop.

43:22.667 --> 43:24.802
[door buzzes]

43:24.836 --> 43:27.038
Or she won't.

43:28.773 --> 43:30.308
‐ Let's go.

43:30.341 --> 43:32.043
‐ It's not your fault.

43:36.080 --> 43:38.983
It's nobody's fault
except hers.

43:39.016 --> 43:43.988
♪ ♪

43:44.021 --> 43:45.389
[door slamming]
